svg.text: In this kind of sentence, sometimes the two occurrences of the question pronoun play
the same grammatical role, i.e, both are subjects, as in (A); or both are objects, as in (B).
Sometimes the two occurrences of the question pronoun perform different grammatical
functions. In (C), for example, the first
is the subject whereas the second
often precedes the verb in the second
clause, but not always, as in (E) and (F) below.
Tā zhǎo shéi bāng tā bān jiājù?
Who’s he going to ask to help him move his furniture?
